document_data.name: Tymora Alley
document_data.mainbody: '''Tymora Alley''' was a small road found in the city of [[Daggerford]] in the [[Western Heartlands]] in the mid-to-late 14{{th}} century [[DR]].{{Cite interactive atlas}}
document_data.Location: Tymora Alley branched south off of [[Wall Street (Daggerford)|Wall Street]] at the midway point between the northern [[Farmer's Gate]] and [[Delfen Ondabarl]]'s tower. Tymora Alley cut south then east before terminating at the landrise that separated the ducal estate from the rest of Daggerford.
document_data.Notable Locations:
Notable buildings located along Tymora Alley included:

* [[Wiston Apothecary]]
